"title": "5556: stewardship",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5556: stewardship",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The careful use, control and management of the possessions of another that have been entrusted to one. The term is also used to refer to the responsible use of wealth and possessions by Christians.</p>\n<h2>Individuals acting as stewards</h2>\n<h3>Adam in the Garden of Eden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:15\">GEN 2:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Joseph in Potiphar's household</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:4-Gen39:6\">GEN 39:4–39:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Daniel as administrator in Babylon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:1-Dan6:3\">DAN 6:1–6:3</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Groups acting as stewards</h2>\n<h3>The priests serving in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:9\">LEV 22:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:15\">1SA 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>The seven chosen by the Jerusalem church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:1–6:6</a></p>\n<h2>Household stewards</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:16\">GEN 43:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:1-Gen44:12\">GEN 44:1–44:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:1\">2SA 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:17\">2SA 19:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:8\">EST 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's teaching on stewardship</h2>\n<h3>Using parables to emphasise accountability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:1-Luke16:12\">LUK 16:1–16:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:14–25:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:27\">LUK 19:12–19:27</a></p>\n<h3>Emphasising each individual's responsibility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:48\">LUK 12:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:36\">MAT 12:36</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles continued this teaching</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:12\">ROM 14:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:4-1Pet4:5\">1PE 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h2>To be a good steward is an honourable thing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:13\">1TI 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:18\">PRO 27:18</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are entrusted with the stewardship of the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:1-1Cor4:2\">1CO 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:17\">1CO 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:19-2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:19–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15-Gal1:16\">GAL 1:15–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7\">GAL 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4\">1TH 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:11\">1TI 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20\">1TI 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:3\">TIT 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:7\">TIT 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are to be wise stewards of their God-given gifts</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:7</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They are to use their gifts to benefit others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10-1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:10–4:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They are to develop their gifts</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14-1Tim4:15\">1TI 4:14–4:15</a></p>\n<h3>They are to care for their bodies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:18-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:18–6:20</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Believers are to be wise stewards of their material possessions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:17-Deut8:18\">DEU 8:17–8:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's teaching on sharing possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:1-Matt6:4\">MAT 6:1–6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19-Matt6:21\">MAT 6:19–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:38\">LUK 6:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:1-Luke21:4\">LUK 21:1–21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a></p>\n<h3>Sharing of possessions among the first Christians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:32–4:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:1-2Cor8:5\">2CO 8:1–8:5</a></p>\n<h3>The apostle Paul's teaching on sharing possessions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:6-2Cor9:11\">2CO 9:6–9:11</a></p>",
